  "text": "In the factor productivity and employee productivity models, the coefficients for diversity are positive and significant, indicating that policies promoting other types of workforce diversity also improve productivity. Consistent with [CITATION_1] , the coefficients for employee relations are positive and significant in all four models. The coefficients for certain other explanatory variables (e.g., size, leverage, investment opportunity, board size, and CEO ownership) are significant in Table 4 , indicating the importance of controlling for these factors in our primary analysis.",
